{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "updatedAt": "2026-06-21T06:52:27.002Z",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For FastAPI + Claude, dependency injection should provide a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "shared"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " Anthropic client plus higher-level services, rather than constructing "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "AsyncAnthropic()"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " inside every route. The cleanest pattern is: create the Claude client once during app startup or as a singleton provider, inject it with "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Depends"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", and build route-facing services on top of that client."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Dependency injection for Claude clients concept diagram",
          "title": null
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What to inject"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In practice, you usually have three dependency layers:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Settings"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " dependency, which provides API key, default model, timeouts, and limits."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "AsyncAnthropic"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " client dependency, which is the low-level Claude SDK client."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "ClaudeService"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " dependency, which wraps the client with app-specific methods like "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "create_message()"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ", "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "stream_message()"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ", or "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "run_tool_loop()"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This gives you a stable route signature such as:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "@router.post(\"/messages\")\nasync def create_message(\n    body: CreateMessageRequest,\n    claude: ClaudeService = Depends(get_claude_service),\n):\n    return await claude.create_message(body)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "That route stays clean because FastAPI resolves the dependency graph automatically and injects the service before your handler runs."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why dependency injection helps"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "FastAPI\u2019s dependency system is designed for shared logic and shared connections, such as database sessions, auth, or external API clients. Claude clients fit this model well because you want:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "A single place to configure the API key and client options."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Consistent defaults across routes."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Easy replacement with mocks in tests."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "No repeated construction logic in handlers."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "FastAPI also caches dependency results within a single request by default, so if multiple downstream dependencies need the same object, they get the same resolved instance for that request without extra work."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Recommended pattern: settings \u2192 client \u2192 service"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A strong pattern is to define dependencies in layers."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "1. Settings dependency"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from pydantic import BaseModel\nimport os\n\nclass Settings(BaseModel):\n    anthropic_api_key: str\n    default_model: str = \"claude-sonnet-4-6\"\n\ndef get_settings() -> Settings:\n    return Settings(\n        anthropic_api_key=os.environ[\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\"],\n        default_model=os.environ.get(\"CLAUDE_MODEL\", \"claude-sonnet-4-6\"),\n    )"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This centralizes all Claude-related configuration into one injectable object."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "2. Claude client dependency"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from anthropic import AsyncAnthropic\nfrom fastapi import Depends\n\ndef get_anthropic_client(\n    settings: Settings = Depends(get_settings),\n) -> AsyncAnthropic:\n    return AsyncAnthropic(api_key=settings.anthropic_api_key)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This works, but it creates a new client whenever the dependency is resolved, which is acceptable for some cases but not ideal if you want a single long-lived shared client."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "3. Claude service dependency"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "class ClaudeService:\n    def __init__(self, client: AsyncAnthropic, settings: Settings):\n        self.client = client\n        self.settings = settings\n\n    async def create_message(self, body):\n        return await self.client.messages.create(\n            model=body.model or self.settings.default_model,\n            max_tokens=body.max_tokens,\n            system=body.system,\n            messages=[m.model_dump() for m in body.messages],\n        )\n\ndef get_claude_service(\n    client: AsyncAnthropic = Depends(get_anthropic_client),\n    settings: Settings = Depends(get_settings),\n) -> ClaudeService:\n    return ClaudeService(client=client, settings=settings)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This gives routes a business-level dependency instead of a raw SDK object, which is usually the better abstraction."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best production pattern: shared client via lifespan"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For production, LLM clients should usually be created once and shared across requests, then exposed through a dependency that retrieves the shared instance. That avoids unnecessary repeated client construction and gives you a stable application-level resource, similar to a shared "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "httpx.AsyncClient"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " pattern."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A practical approach is to create the Claude client in FastAPI\u2019s lifespan and store it on "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "app.state"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Lifespan setup"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from contextlib import asynccontextmanager\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI\nfrom anthropic import AsyncAnthropic\nimport os\n\n@asynccontextmanager\nasync def lifespan(app: FastAPI):\n    app.state.anthropic_client = AsyncAnthropic(\n        api_key=os.environ[\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\"]\n    )\n    yield\n    # If future SDK versions expose explicit close/cleanup, do it here.\n\napp = FastAPI(lifespan=lifespan)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This pattern matches the general FastAPI guidance for long-lived shared resources and is specifically recommended in LLM-client DI guidance for FastAPI agent systems."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Dependency to retrieve shared client"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from fastapi import Request\n\ndef get_anthropic_client(request: Request) -> AsyncAnthropic:\n    return request.app.state.anthropic_client"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This keeps the dependency tiny and ensures every route gets the same shared client instance."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Service dependency using shared client"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def get_claude_service(\n    request: Request,\n    settings: Settings = Depends(get_settings),\n) -> ClaudeService:\n    client: AsyncAnthropic = request.app.state.anthropic_client\n    return ClaudeService(client=client, settings=settings)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This is my preferred FastAPI + Claude pattern because it keeps lifecycle management at the app level and app behavior at the service level."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Route usage pattern"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Once dependencies are set up, routes stay small and consistent:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from fastapi import APIRouter, Depends\n\nrouter = APIRouter(prefix=\"/messages\", tags=[\"messages\"])\n\n@router.post(\"\")\nasync def create_message(\n    body: CreateMessageRequest,\n    claude: ClaudeService = Depends(get_claude_service),\n):\n    return await claude.create_message(body)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For streaming:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "@router.post(\"/stream\")\nasync def stream_message(\n    body: CreateMessageRequest,\n    claude: ClaudeService = Depends(get_claude_service),\n):\n    return await claude.stream_sse(body)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This is exactly what DI is meant for in FastAPI: routes declare what they need, and the framework resolves those dependencies for you."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Request-scoped vs app-scoped dependencies"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This distinction matters:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "App-scoped/shared client"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": best for the Anthropic client itself, because it is a reusable infrastructure object."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Request-scoped service objects"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": fine for "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "ClaudeService"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ", because it may combine the shared client with request-specific context like user, tenant, auth, or tracing metadata."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "So the pattern is usually:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Shared "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "AsyncAnthropic"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Per-request "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "ClaudeService"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Per-request subdependencies like "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "current_user"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ", "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "tenant_context"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ", or "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "request_id"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This lets you keep connection-like resources global while business context stays request-specific."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Sub-dependencies for auth and tenant-aware Claude use"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "FastAPI dependencies can depend on other dependencies, so you can compose Claude services with security and tenancy naturally."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For example:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "class TenantContext(BaseModel):\n    tenant_id: str\n    model_override: str | None = None\n\nasync def get_tenant_context(...) -> TenantContext:\n    ...\n\ndef get_claude_service(\n    client: AsyncAnthropic = Depends(get_anthropic_client),\n    settings: Settings = Depends(get_settings),\n    tenant: TenantContext = Depends(get_tenant_context),\n) -> ClaudeService:\n    return ClaudeService(client=client, settings=settings, tenant=tenant)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This is useful when different tenants have different model policies, token budgets, or feature flags."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Testing benefits"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "One of the biggest reasons to use DI for Claude clients is testability. FastAPI supports dependency overrides, so you can replace the real Claude client or service with a fake in tests."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Example:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from fastapi.testclient import TestClient\n\nclass FakeClaudeService:\n    async def create_message(self, body):\n        return {\"content\": \"fake response\"}\n\napp.dependency_overrides[get_claude_service] = lambda: FakeClaudeService()\n\nclient = TestClient(app)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This lets you test routing, validation, and response formatting without touching the real Anthropic API."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Anti-patterns"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Avoid these common mistakes:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Creating "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "AsyncAnthropic()"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " directly inside every route handler, which duplicates setup and makes testing harder."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Mixing environment variable reads into many modules instead of a settings dependency."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Injecting the raw client everywhere when most routes really need a higher-level service abstraction."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Treating every dependency as a global singleton, including request-specific state, which makes multi-tenant or auth-aware behavior messy."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Using "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Depends(..., use_cache=False)"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " unnecessarily for shared resources, which defeats normal request-level reuse."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Recommended blueprint"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For FastAPI + Claude, the most maintainable dependency injection blueprint is:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "get_settings()"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2192 returns app config."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "lifespan()"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2192 creates one shared "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "AsyncAnthropic"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " client."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "get_anthropic_client(request)"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2192 returns that shared client."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "get_current_user()"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " / "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "get_tenant_context()"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2192 request-specific dependencies."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "get_claude_service(...)"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2192 composes client + settings + request context into a service."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Routes depend on "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "ClaudeService"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ", not directly on the SDK client."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "That gives you clean routes, centralized Claude configuration, correct lifecycle management, and easy test overrides\u2014the four main goals of dependency injection in a FastAPI + Claude backend."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best Practices"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When working with dependency injection for claude clients, following established best practices ensures reliability, maintainability, and optimal performance."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Start simple and iterate \u2014 begin with the minimum viable implementation before adding complexity."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Test with representative inputs \u2014 ensure your test cases cover edge cases, not just the happy path."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Monitor performance \u2014 track latency, token usage, and error rates in production environments."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Version your prompts and configurations \u2014 treat prompt text like source code with proper version control."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Document your design decisions \u2014 record why you chose specific approaches for future maintainers."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Plan for failure \u2014 implement graceful degradation when the AI component is unavailable or returns unexpected results."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Review outputs regularly \u2014 periodically audit what the system produces to catch quality drift over time."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common Mistakes to Avoid"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "These pitfalls frequently trip up developers working with dependency injection for claude clients. Knowing them in advance saves significant debugging time."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Assuming deterministic output \u2014 language models are probabilistic; the same input can produce different outputs across calls. Always validate the structure of responses."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Ignoring token limits \u2014 exceeding context window limits causes truncation or errors. Track token counts, especially in multi-turn conversations."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Over-engineering early \u2014 building complex infrastructure before validating basic functionality wastes effort. Get a working prototype first."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Hardcoding prompts in code \u2014 embed prompts in configuration files or databases so non-developers can iterate on them."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Skipping error handling \u2014 API calls fail due to rate limits, timeouts, or content policy violations. Always wrap calls in try/catch with appropriate retry logic."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Performance and Scalability"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "As your usage of dependency injection for claude clients scales, these performance factors become increasingly important."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Latency budget \u2014 typical API latency ranges from 1-30 seconds depending on model size and output length. Design your UX around streaming to provide early feedback."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Concurrency limits \u2014 each API tier has request-per-minute (RPM) and token-per-minute (TPM) limits. Implement request queuing for burst traffic."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Prompt caching \u2014 use the cache_control breakpoint on stable, repeated prompt prefixes to reduce costs by up to 90% and latency by 85%."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Batching \u2014 for non-interactive workloads, the Message Batches API processes up to 10,000 requests asynchronously at 50% cost reduction."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Model selection \u2014 use Claude Haiku for high-volume, low-complexity tasks and Claude Sonnet or Opus for complex reasoning where quality matters more than speed."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}